Automated Underground Coal Mining Ventilation System
Project Overview
This project focuses on developing an automated ventilation system for underground coal mines to improve safety.

Problem
Underground mines release dangerous gases like methane (CH4) and carbon monoxide (CO). Manual ventilation systems are slow and unsafe.

Solution
This system uses:

ESP32 microcontroller

MQ-4 gas sensor (Methane)

MQ-7 gas sensor (CO)

DHT11 temperature sensor

12V fan

Relay module

OLED display

Buzzer

Working
Sensors detect gas levels.

ESP32 checks threshold.

If gas level is high:

Fan turns ON

Buzzer gives alert

If safe:

Fan stays OFF.

Total Cost
₹3434 (Low-cost prototype)

Result
The system successfully detects gas and automatically controls ventilation to improve safety.

